'''Solar energy in Poland''' includes the production of [[solar thermal]] energy and [[solar photovoltaics]]. Solar thermal, used for heating water, used {{convert|1700000|m2|ft2}} of installed [[solar thermal collector]]s at the end of 2014. This corresponds to about 1,200&nbsp;[[Megawatt|MW]]<sub>[[MWt|th]]</sub> capacity. Solar collectors are the second largest source of renewable heat in Poland, after biomass heating plants. In 2014, Poland was ranked fourth in sales of solar collector installations among European countries.<ref>[http://gramwzielone.pl/trendy/17118/polska-4-najwiekszym-rynkiem-kolektorow-slonecznych-w-europie-w-2014 Poland 4th biggest market of solar collectors in Europe in 2014]</ref>
The total [[solar photovoltaics]] (PV) grid-connected capacity in Poland was 1,299 MW at the end of 2019.<ref name=PV2019/>
